                            <comment id="12850338" author="srowen" created="Fri, 26 Mar 2010 20:26:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good one &amp;#8211; the hashed index needs to have its top bit cleared to ensure its nonnegative. I just submitted a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850873" author="huiwenhan" created="Mon, 29 Mar 2010 11:31:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;There still has error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850886" author="srowen" created="Mon, 29 Mar 2010 12:07:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ugh, I think I see the problem with my too-quick fix. I changed the expression:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(int) itemID ^ (int) (itemID &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; 32)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0x7FFFFFFF &amp;amp; (int) itemID ^ (int) (itemID &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; 32)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but due to order of operations this isn&apos;t doing what it&apos;s supposed to. It should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0x7FFFFFFF &amp;amp; ((int) itemID ^ (int) (itemID &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; 32))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Try one more time. You are regenerating all of the data from scratch right, not reusing old output files?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850889" author="huiwenhan" created="Mon, 29 Mar 2010 12:32:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I do not use the old output file ,&lt;br/&gt;
I will try the new one right now.&lt;br/&gt;
very thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
